"If a country is to be corruption free and become a nation of beautiful minds, I strongly feel there are three key societal members who can make a difference. They are the father, the mother, and the teacher." – APJ Abdul Kalam
  After our parents, the most important role is played by teachers in the process of our learning about life around us. The definition of a teacher is not restricted to the ones bounded with the walls of a classroom, the word imbibes into every personality who has a positive influence on you till eternity. It is, therefore, important to recognize the role played by teachers in our formative years and Teacher’s Day is the day that all students celebrate to acknowledge the hardship, challenges and the unparalleled role that the teachers play in our lives. In India, Teachers’ Day is celebrated on September 5 to mark the birthday of former President, politician, scholar, philosopher, and Bharat Ratna recipient, Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan, who was born on the same day in 1888.
 No matter how old we grow, the lessons taught by our teachers can never be forgotten. They build the foundation for our moral values and nurture children with their love and care. This Teachers' day, ISTE NIT Durgapur students’ chapter thanks all the teachers for making our world so perfect. Feel proud and honored to celebrate Teachers' day.
 #education #happyteacherday #nitdgp #teachers

Muharram, the day of ceremonial mourning also called Ashura is observed by Shia muslims all over the world. The bravery and the sacrifice of Hussain Ibn Ali, grandson of Prophet Muhammad in the form of his life in the battlefield of Karbala is remembered and in this regard the Shia Muslims also beat themselves with sharp objects. This act is a symbol of the sufferings experienced by the Prophet's grandson. Shia Muslims also dress up in black and many muslims also observe a partial fast. This is also a symbol of struggle against injustice and oppression. 
  Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur ,pays its homage expressing grief on the inhuman tortures experienced urging everyone to fight unitedly against all kinds of injustices existing in the society to make this world a better place to live in.

A proud moment for us at NIT Durgapur as the world's first helium gas exploration plant is going to be set up at Bakreshwar in a collaboration between the Atomic Minerals Directorate and our college, ending years of dependence on costly helium gas imports from the USA. Kudos to Dr Hirok Chaudhuri, associate professor of Department of Physics and Centre for Research on Environment and Water and our Director Professor Anupam Basu from our college for working on the initiative. The project is expected to be completed within 3 years. This is an article from The Statesman.

Link to the article : https://www.thestatesman.com/bengal/worlds-first-helium-gas-exploration-plant-coming-bakreswar-1502919930.html

#TheStatesman
#HeliumGasExploration
#NITDurgapur

"गणपति बप्पा मोरया, मंगल मूर्ति मोरया" 
Ganesh Chaturthi , one of the most sacred festivals of the country is celebrated to commemorate the birth anniversary of Lord Ganesha. Also known as Vinayak Chaturthi, it is celebrated all over the country with remarkable  enthusiasm , grandeur and merriment as an epitome of wisdom, prosperity and good fortune. Starting from making clay idols of Lord Ganesha to various rituals and offerings including modak, coconut rice, laddoo , this festival continues for a period of 10 days serving as the driving force of unity among us bridging the gap created by narrow domestic walls. 
 With the world facing a devastating  pandemic and several crisis , we , ISTE NIT Durgapur, pray to Lord with a hope that we will pull through these hurdles and miseries unitedly and again the world would be a beautiful place to live in. Wishing everyone Happy Ganesh Chaturthi!!

#ganeshchaturthi #india #istenitdgp #ISTE

Our country again set an example of excellence in the field of advanced technology and space research. Skyroot, India's first private space launch startup carried out the test fire of "Raman", an upper stage rocket engine, with remarkable success on the 12th of August. Through the use of 3-D printing technology for the first time , not only was the number of components were reduced but also the overall mass and lead time. According to the company, it aims at having a launch of its first rocket by end of next year. ISTE NIT Durgapur congratulates Skyroot for such a great achievement and hopes that our space research would be more enriched in the future through such endeavours.

#India #innovations #istenitdgp #ISTE

“At the stroke of the midnight hour, when the world sleeps, India will awake to life and freedom." This independence was the fruit of bold and selfless struggle of our freedom fighters who paved the way for a peaceful and happy life which we enjoy. Since then we have come a long way forward becoming world’s largest democracy. Still , we are surrounded with numerous social, economic, political problems which hinder our progress. In several areas like defense, electronic goods, advanced machinery, India imports mostly from other countries. In addition, there is a growing unemployment and poverty .This leads to an economic bondage obstructing our goal of complete Independence.  Thus we should act in accordance with the policy devised by our Prime Minister for making India “Self Reliant” and strive through incorporation of innovation, advanced technology, scientific know-how devising plans and acting accordingly to pull through such a hazardous situation. 
Therefore, on the occasion of the 74th Independence Day, ISTE NIT Durgapur urges everyone to take a firm pledge as patriots of our motherland , plunging into the service of the nation so that we can truly realize the dream which our freedom fighters had seen laying the foundation of a “Heaven of Freedom”.
#happyindependenceday #sacrifice #festival #nitdgp #işte #joy

Google has released a new feature for mobile users named 'People Cards'. This will allow you to create a virtual business card which will be visible to anyone who search for your name on Google. This feature is aimed at individuals, influencers, entrepreneurs, prospective employees, self-employed people and freelancers, who want to be discovered.

How to get yourself one:

Step 1 - Sign in to your google account using a mobile device (this is a mobile only feature).
Step 2 - Search "your name" on google search.
Step 3 - Tap on the 'add me to search' option that appears on the page.
Step 4 - Upload a photo of yourself on your google account (if you already haven't). Add the details that the form asks for. Categories marked '*' are mandatory. Skip the rest if you want to. Click preview and then save your profile. 
Step 5 - You should now be able to see your card when you search for your name in Google Search. The card will appear on public searches after a few days, once Google has confirmed its authenticity.

#google #peoplescard #istenitdgp

node.text: Krishna Janmasthami , is one of the most gala occasions of the Hindus, which is commemorated to glorify, the birth ceremony of Lord Krishna , the eighth Avatar of Shri Vishnu. And it is generally observed on the eighth day of Krishna Paskha , in accordance to the Hindu Lunisolar Calenders. Lord Krishna, symbolizes compassion, tenderness, love and is one of the most popular and widely revered among Indian divinities. The decorum of Janmasthami , panegyrizes the nativity of both Krishna and Durga to demolish all the iniquity and transgression of Kansa. While Krishna came to Devaki, Durga came to Yasodha. And the Hindu texts are luminescenced through the perpetuity , of the exertion and grind of Bosudev and Vasuki , lead the cherubim Krishna to NandGaon. And soul always triggers of how Goddess Shakti transformed from a newborn to Kansa , when Kansa wanted to stab the baby , brought by Bosudev. The roman-fleuve is ad-infinitum. But empathetically for aeons Krishna Janmasthami , designates the rise of the empyrean aura , which would dismantle all the egregious viles from the world. This year, assuredly we all pray wholeheartedly to disassemble the COVID-19 and also the subversive and noxious maligns existent in our society. With dulia and latria from the inner chords of our hearts, ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER , put forward our vespers to Lord Krishna and wishes everyone the numinous empyrean benelovence and altruism on the juncture of Krishna Janmasthami.

Sir Alexander Fleming ,a Scottish bacteriologist was a genius for his technical ingenuity and original observation. His work on wound infection and lysozyme, an antibacterial enzyme found in tears and saliva, guaranteed him a place in the history of bacteriology. But it was his discovery of penicillin in 1928, which started the antibiotic revolution providing him lasting reputation. Fleming was recognized for that achievement in 1945, when he received the Nobel Prize for Physiology or Medicine, along with Howard Walter Florey and Ernst Boris Chain, both of whom isolated and purified penicillin. It was a discovery that changed the course of history. The active ingredient in that mould which Fleming named penicillin, turned out to be an infection-fighting agent of enormous potency. When it was finally recognized for what it was, the most efficacious life-saving drug in the world, penicillin altered forever the treatment of bacterial infections.
 Today, 6th Aug is the Birthday of this greatest human soul. Therefore,on this auspicious day,ISTE NIT Durgapur Students’ Chapter pays homage to Sir Alexander Fleming for his achievements and contribution to the world of science.

Raksha Bandhan is a popular, traditionally Hindu, annual rite, or ceremony, which is central to a festival of the same name, celebrated in different parts of the Indian subcontinent, and among people around the world influenced by Hindu culture. On this day, sisters of all ages tie a talisman, or amulet, called the rakhi or raksha, around the wrists of their brothers, symbolically protecting them, receiving a gift in return, and traditionally investing the brothers with a share of the responsibility of their potential care. However "Raksha Bandhan" has a different significance in the context of the Indian mythology. It was when Draupadi tied a piece of cloth to Shri Krishna , who was her friend's brother, signifying her protective spirit and marking the start of this ritual.

The expression "Raksha Bandhan," Sanskrit, literally, "the bond of protection, obligation, or care," is now principally applied to this ritual.

Thus, ISTE NIT Durgapur Students Chapter heartily wishes all sisters and brothers a happy "Raksha Bandhan". May the spirit of closeness, responsibility and protection between cousins and siblings remain unfazed through the test of time.
#rakshabandhan #festival #işte #nitdgp

Eid ul Adha is a sacred Muslim event that is celebrated every year around the world in the month of hajj on the 10th of Zil hajj after all the pilgrims to Makkah have performed the obligatory events. The sole purpose of this event is to earn countless blessings of Allah by sacrificing animals in the way of Allah, completing the rituals of Hajj and offering the Eid al Adha prayer . This Eid reminds us of the sacrifice that Prophet Abraham was willing to make for the sake of Allah. This also provides us an idea of the quality of faith that we should have in our one and only God. Distributing the meat from the sacrifice helps us to promotes love and brotherhood, and allows the people to realize that they should be thankful to Allah for all the bounties that have been provided.
 On this very holy occasion, ISTE NIT Durgapur Student's Chapter wishes "Happy Eid" to all. “No shadows to depress you. Only joys to surround you. Allah himself to bless you. These are my wishes for you. Today tomorrow and every day… Eid Mubarak!”

#eidmubarak #istenitdgp

Kargil Vijay Diwas is celebrated on 26 July to commemorate the victory of the Indian soldiers over the infiltrating Pakistani troops. On 3rd of May, 1999 , Pakistan started this war and it was fought for more than 60 days, ending on 26 July and resulted in loss of life on both the sides. The war ended with India regaining the  control over all the previously held territories, hence re-establishing the the state existing before the war.
 It would not be wrong to say that  War is never good. It causes  major losses on both sides. India is a peace-loving country that does not believe in war. Indian army always safeguards the nation from alien forces, sacrifice for the Motherland, and make us proud.
 "TOUGH TIMES DON'T LAST,BUT TOUGH MEN DO"
 In This memorable day ISTE Students’ Chapter NIT Durgapur  pays homage to the Kargil martyrs. This is the day to remember the supreme sacrifice made by our brave soldiers to uphold and safeguard the integrity of the nation. Huge respect to entire Indian Armed Force for all their sacrifices and brave deeds. JAI HIND!!

#kargilvijaydiwas #indianarmy #army #sacrifice
